main event: During March to June 1952, several unidentified aerial objects were reported in the San Diego, California area, described as flying at extremely high speeds and altitudes, and performing maneuvers not characteristic of conventional aircraft.
interesting points: The objects were metallic in appearance and varied in size from approximately 30 to 50 feet in length.
Multiple reliable and competent observers reported the sightings over a period of several days.
The source of information, an experienced air observer, reported these sightings.
The objects were observed to be flying at extremely high speeds and altitudes and left no vapor trail.
The report includes a detailed diagram and handwritten calculations related to a UFO sighting, indicating a high level of effort in documenting the event.
sighted object: Several unidentified aerial objects described as flying at high speeds and performing unconventional maneuvers
witnesses: Experienced air observer and other members of a private club in San Diego
